RACE.FOOTNOTES: COMMANDER REX came in slightly at the start carrying PROMISE CODE in then saved ground setting the pace, responded when challenged by FRIDAYNIGHTSOLDIER nearing the quarter pole and proved best under strong handling. FRIDAYNIGHTSOLDIER saved ground while racing close up early, angled out two-wide to offer a bid nearing the quarter pole, gained a slight lead between calls in the stretch but wasn't quite good enough. KENTUCKY ICE was bumped by PROMISE CODE and pinched back when COMMANDER REX came in, then was unhurried early, rallied five-wide the final quarter and finished fast. EL SMOOCH was allowed to settle in stride while racing two-wide and went evenly. PROMISE CODE was carried in by the winner at the start bumping with KENTUCKY ICE, then settled in the middle of the field, came four-wide into the stretch but lacked a rally. XKUZ prompted the early pace from along the outside and tired. ABES DAY dropped back early then came three-wide into the stretch and failed to threaten. NATIVE MOONSHINE was off a step slow, then rushed up to show brief speed, gave way badly after a quarter mile and was eased in the stretch and walked off following the race. THE RIDER OF KENTUCKY ICE LODGED AN OBJECTION AGAINST COMMANDER REX FOR INTERFERENCE AT THE START BUT AFTER VIEWING THE FILMS THE STEWARDS RULED THAT KENTUCKY ICE WOULD NOT OF BEATEN COMMANDER REX WITHOUT THE INTERFERENCE SO MADE NO CHANGE IN THE ORDER OF FINISH.
